alltests -- run arbitrary command on the set of tests

## Description: TODO

## Requirements:

* Two other scripts (by the same author) to be in PATH: nice_paste, runcpp
* Unix commands to be available: find, sed, time, rm (nothing user's will be removed)


## Examples (aplusb):

$ alltests python2 sum.py

Will run command 'python2 sum.py' on the given set of tests (test/*.in)
and compare outputs with corresponding files (test/*.out)


$ alltests

Will automatically find source file. If several available random is choosen. Python source code has precedence over C++
Thus, it's equivalent to the previous example (./alltests python sum.py)


$ alltests --cpp sum.cpp --abort-on-fail

Aborts on the first test that is not passed


$ alltests --cpp sum.cpp --short

Will print only results of tests, no stdout/correct answer


$ alltests --help

Try it for more details


## Examples (sort):

$ alltests python sort.py

Nice, but what if...


$ alltests sort  # unix sort command

It works! You can specify any command!
